			<h1 class="govuk-heading-l govuk-!-margin-bottom-8 hsm-heading-1">More information about this service</h1>

            <section class="hsm-about-page-section hsm-about-page-section-who govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
                <h2 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-margin-bottom-5 hsm-heading-1">Who this service is intended for?</h2>
                <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-3">This service is intended for anybody who is responsible for their homes heating system who can decide on the upgrades undertaken on this system. Therefore, it is intended for owner occupiers and landlords.</p>
                <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-3">If you rent your home as a social or private tenant, you may also use this service to inform yourself and your landlord of available options however, the responsibility for upgrading the heating system will usually sit with your landlord.</p>
                <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-3">If you live in a park home then you will be able to use this service through all stages however, the result will return that heat pumps are not suitable for your home.</p>
                <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-3">If you currently use a communal or district heating system then you can still use this service however, some of the content may not be relevant to your home and some of the results such as the carbon emissions may not be an accurate reflection for your home.</p>
                <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-3">If you live in a mobile home such as a van, caravan or houseboat, heat pumps are not suited to your home and this service does not have the option to select this type of home. </p>
                <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-3">If you already have a heat pump installation, please visit <a href="@Model.McsCertifiedUrl" class="govuk-link">MCS</a>  to find designers and installers. rather than using this service.</p>
            </section>
            
            <section class="hsm-about-page-section hsm-about-page-section-overview govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
				<h2 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-margin-bottom-5 hsm-heading-1">How this service works - Overview</h2>
                <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-3">This service uses the details you input about your home alongside reference data from the BEIS funded Electrification of Heat Demonstration Project to approximate which Heat Pumps options could be suitable for installation in your home and how much they might cost.</p>
                <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-3">It also estimates how the installation of a heat pump may affect the carbon emissions associated with heating your home. It does this by comparing the fuel used in your current heating system to the electricity used to power a heat pump, it then estimates the efficiency of both your current heating system and a heat pump and calculates the relative carbon emissions per unit (kWh) of heat produced.</p>
                <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-3">Finally, based on your answers to the questions, the service presents potential home upgrades which may enable a heat pump to operate efficiently in your home and predicts an associated cost of these home upgrades.</p>
			</section>
            
