                <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
                    <li>The heat pump cost data was sourced from the BEIS Electrification of Heat Demonstration Project.</li>
                    <li>The Analysis Engine calculates the heat pump size, and presents the associated cost, based upon data sourced from the BEIS Electrification of Heat Demonstration Project.</li>
                    <li>The heat pump efficiencies used in the carbon calculations are inferred from the Renewable Heat Premium Payment project, the Renewable Energy Consumer Code and the MCS database. These will be updated with Electrification of Heat values once they are calculated.
                    </li>
                    <li>The efficiency of other heating systems is estimated using Tables 4a and 4b of The Governmentâ€™s Standard Assessment Procedure for Energy Rating of Dwellings 2012 (SAP 2012) found at: <a href="@Model.EnergyRatingOfDwellings2012Url" class="govuk-link hsm-wrap">@Model.EnergyRatingOfDwellings2012Url</a></li>
                    <li>The carbon factors used to compare carbon emissions are the BEIS Greenhouse gas reporting: conversion factors 2021 found at: <a href="@Model.BEISGreenhouseGasReportingUrl" class="govuk-link hsm-wrap">@Model.BEISGreenhouseGasReportingUrl</a></li>
